history.content:
Jane Street is back and will be hosting a dinner at UC Berkeley!


Wednesday, February 16 @ 6pm PT
Location: Berkeley, CA


Interested in learning more about Jane Street? Students of all backgrounds and tenures are encouraged to attend - you don't need experience in finance to work at Jane Street. We hope to meet intellectually curious problem solvers!


IMPORTANT: Please sign up here by Wednesday, February 9th @ 11:59pm PT, if you're interested in attending. We will confirm attendees by EOD on Monday, February 14th - we hope to see you there!


COVID-19 Protocols: All attendees must be fully vaccinated* in order to attend. This event will be fully outdoors and masks will not be required, but they're always appropriate.


You should only register if you are comfortable with attending an in-person event. If not, you should feel at ease passing on this opportunity as it will not have any bearing on your candidacy with Jane Street. We will have other opportunities to meet in the future.


_______________


Jane Street is a quantitative trading firm with offices worldwide. They hire smart, humble people who love to solve problems, build systems, and test theories. You’ll learn something new every day in their office—whether it’s connecting with a colleague to share perspectives, or participating in a talk, class, or game night. Their success is driven by our people and we never stop improving.
Want to learn more? Check out their virtual info booth.
